TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bodurtha, James N., Jr
AU  - Kim, Dong-Soon
AU  - Lee, Charles M.C.
T1  - Closed-end Country Funds and U.S. Market Sentiment
PY  - 1995
Y1  - 1995/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/8.3.879
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 8
IS  - 3
SP  - 879
EP  - 918
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Closed-end country funds can trade at large premiums and discounts from their foreign asset values (NAVs). Investigating this anomaly, we find that individual fund premiums move together, primarily because of the comovement of their stock prices with the U.S. market. Moreover, an index of country fund premiums differentiates size-ranked U.S. portfolio returns and forecasts country fund stock returns. These findings suggest that international equity prices are affected by local risk. In particular, we show that country fund premium movements reflect a U.S.-specific risk, which may be interpreted as U.S. market sentiment.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/8.3.879
ER  - 



